# Get key: https://trello.com/app-key
# Token: same page → generate token (read your boards)
# Board id: open a board, URL is trello.com/b/BOARD_ID/… (8-char) or use the 24-char id from the board menu → More → Print and export
TRELLO_API_KEY=
TRELLO_TOKEN=
# One board or comma-separated: board1,board2
TRELLO_BOARD_ID=

# Optional: cache Trello id list (minutes). Default 15
# TRELLO_CACHE_MINUTES=15

# Optional: skip check for one command: set SKIP_TRELLO_VALIDATE=1
# (Or use git commit with hooks disabled: git -c core.hooksPath=/dev/null commit …)

# — After a *successful* push, comment commit links on Trello (optional) —
# Comma-separated branch names. When you push to one of them, each new commit
# whose message starts with "SHORTID - " gets a comment on that Trello card.
# Required for Trello links after `npm run git:push` (use your real branch name):
# TRELLO_POST_PUSH_BRANCHES=main
# TRELLO_DEBUG=1
# Re-generate the token with write scope so comments can be posted.
# Test key/token: npm run trello:smoke
# TRELLO_COMMIT_BASE_URL=https://github.com/ORG/REPO
# (Auto-detected from remote.origin.url for many GitHub-style URLs. Non-GitHub: set this explicitly.)
# SKIP_TRELLO_POST=1
# TRELLO_STRICT_POST=1
#
# Trello runs only after the network push succeeds. Use:
#   npm run git:push -- [same args you would pass to git push]
# Plain `git push` runs pre-push (build) but will not post to Trello afterward.
# If a push fails or is "already up to date", no Trello comment is added.
